Installation notes
==================

* Unpack the .tar.gz archive.
* Install the latest version of node.js and the npm package manager.
* Within the javascript folder, install the nod.js serialport module.
* From within the bin folder, run the shell script with the command line parameters:
  * -monitor if you want monitoring
  * path to the serialport
  * baudrate
  * tcp/ip port number
* Use telnet to connect to localhost on the specified port
* Press ctrl-c within the console for terminating the program.